rComments: Loved her class. She's genuinely nice, a pretty generous marker comparatively, and always happy to clarify anything I had issues with. Made the course work simple and straightforward without oversimplifying it. No textbook as everything is posted online. Better than most profs I've had.

Lots of work but the content is simple. Interesting lectures. Detailed textbook notes and lecture notes (keep writing for the whole class- the slides are key points only and won't tell you much) will pretty much guarantee your mark. Prof. Mangalindan is also very helpful with e-mails, in office hours, and when you ask for clarification in class.

Although as a person, she is very kind and seems to genuinely care for her students, she is a BORING lecturer! Quiet and not engaging. It's unfortunate 40% of tests are lecture-based material. Her slides do not help.  Vaguely worded questions that confuse you or are way too specific. I would not recommend.

Lectures are easy but tests are brutal. Some of the questions are worded vaguely which can confuse a student. The easy lectures give an illusion that the tests will be easy too but this is not the case. Tests are not fair. Lecture content could be finished in 1 hour but the prof drags it till 2 and a half hours. Text book content is fun to read.
Lectures were too packed with information, three full hours and she always goes too fast for note taking. Very nice and helpful though
Really nice professor and helpful! Really enjoyed taking class with her
